HEADWORD: Eburin
<hw>Eb"ur*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A composition of dust
of ivory or of bone with a cement; -- used for imitations of valuable
stones and in making moldings, seals, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

